Capuchins Daily Trajectories

Daily travel in plantations and INP

AKDE HMM Index

We compared the daily trajectories of black capuchins in pine plantations vs INP to investigate how travel distances reflect movement patterns and ecological requirements in contrasting landscapes. The availability and spatial distribution of sleeping sites are recognized as critical factors influencing the daily movement patterns of arboreal primates, determining where individuals begin and end their activity periods (Fruth et al., 2018). To integrate this factor into our analysis, we calculated the straight-line distance between the morning and evening sleeping sites, which were defined as locations recorded within 15 min after sunrise or before sunset. Daily sunrise and sunset times were computed using the suncalc R package (Thieurmel et al., 2019), ensuring temporal accuracy across the study period. Only complete tracking days were included in the analysis, defined as days with eight evenly spaced locations recorded at 90-minute intervals (15 minutes), capturing the full extent of daily activity.

2.1 Calculating Steps

First I am creating the SF object to extract UTM coordinates (\(X\) and \(Y\)), using complex number then I obtain \(Z = X + iY\). The total daily trajectory includes the sum of all steps conducted within a same day. There are still some strange data that showed length above 7000 m, these days were removed becuase there were linked to location that not are from the monkeys (inside buildings for instance)

locs_sf <- locs_full_day %>% 
  st_as_sf(coords = c('lon', 'lat'), crs = 4326) %>% 
  st_transform(crs = 32721)

locs_sf_coords <- st_coordinates(locs_sf)

locs_full_day <- locs_full_day %>% 
  mutate(
    X = locs_sf_coords[,"X"],
    Y = locs_sf_coords[,"Y"],
    Z = X + 1i * Y
  )

steps_data <- locs_full_day %>%
  group_by(area, id, date) %>%
  arrange(t, .by_group = TRUE) %>%  
  mutate(S = c(Mod(diff(Z)), NA)) %>%  
  summarise(
    mean_S = mean(S, na.rm = TRUE),   
    sd_S = sd(S, na.rm = TRUE),       
    sum_S = sum(S, na.rm = TRUE),
    prop_plantations = mean(tipouso_grouped == "plantations", na.rm = TRUE),
    .groups = "drop"
  )

steps_data <- steps_data %>%
  filter(sum_S < 7000)

locs_first_last <- locs_full_day %>%
  group_by(id, date) %>%

  mutate(time_label = "first") %>%  
  bind_rows(
    locs_full_day %>%
      group_by(id, date) %>%

      mutate(time_label = "last")   
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

locs_full_day <- locs_full_day %>%
  mutate(date = as.Date(date))

get_sun_times <- function(date, lat, lon) {
  sun_times <- getSunlightTimes(
    date = date, lat = lat, lon = lon,
    keep = c("sunrise", "sunset"),
    tz = "America/Argentina/Buenos_Aires")
  return(sun_times)
}

sun_times_list <- pmap(
  list(locs_full_day$date, locs_full_day$lat, locs_full_day$lon),
  get_sun_times)

  locs_first_last %>%
  left_join(sun_data_unique, by = "month_join") %>%
  mutate(
    
    t_horario = as.POSIXct(paste("2024-01-01", horario)),
    sunrise_period = as.POSIXct(paste("2024-01-01", sunrise_horario)),
    sunset_period = as.POSIXct(paste("2024-01-01", sunset_horario)),
    
    t_to_sunrise = if_else(
      time_label == "first",
      as.numeric(difftime(
        t_horario,
        sunrise_period,
        units = "mins")),
      NA_real_),
    t_to_sunset = if_else(
      time_label == "last", 
      as.numeric(difftime(
        sunset_period,
        t_horario, 
        units = "mins")),
      NA_real_)) 

locs_with_sun_info <- locs_with_sun_info %>%
  dplyr::select(-sunrise_period, sunset_period, sunset,sunrise)

locs_with_sun_info <- locs_with_sun_info %>%
  mutate(
    time_to_sun = coalesce(t_to_sunrise, t_to_sunset)) %>%
  dplyr::select(-t_to_sunrise, -t_to_sunset)


locs_with_sun <- locs_with_sun_info %>%
  filter(time_to_sun >= -15 & time_to_sun <= 15)

2.4 Distances between sleeping sites (euclicean distances)

locs_with_sun <- locs_with_sun %>%
  group_by(id, date.x) %>%
  mutate(
    X_first = na_if(first(X[time_label == "first"]), NA),
    Y_first = na_if(first(Y[time_label == "first"]), NA),
    X_last = na_if(first(X[time_label == "last"]), NA),
    Y_last = na_if(first(Y[time_label == "last"]), NA),
    
    distance_ss = if_else(
      !is.na(X_first) & !is.na(Y_first) & !is.na(X_last) & !is.na(Y_last),
      sqrt((X_last - X_first)^2 + (Y_last - Y_first)^2),
      NA_real_
    )
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  dplyr::select(-X_first, -Y_first, -X_last, -Y_last)

3.2 Models

m0 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ 1 + (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)
m1 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area + (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)
m2 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area + distance_ss_scaled + (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)
m3 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area * distance_ss_scaled + (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)
m4 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area * food + distance_ss_scaled +  (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)
m5 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area * distance_ss_scaled + food +  (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)
m6 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area + t_min_scaled + (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)
m7 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area + t_min_scaled + precip_scaled + (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)
m8 <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area + distance_ss_scaled + t_min_scaled + precip_scaled + (1 | grupo), data = locs_day)

set.seed(123)


folds <- createFolds(locs_day$sum_S2, k = 10, list = TRUE)


errors <- numeric(length(folds))


for (i in seq_along(folds)) {
  train_data <- locs_day[-folds[[i]], ] 
  test_data <- locs_day[folds[[i]], ]  
  

  model <- lmer(sum_S2 ~ area * distance_ss_scaled + food + t_min_scaled + 
                  precip_scaled + (1 | grupo),
                data = train_data)  # Aqu usamos train_data
  

  predictions <- predict(model, newdata = test_data, allow.new.levels = TRUE)
  

  errors[i] <- mean((predictions - test_data$sum_S2)^2, na.rm = TRUE)
}

mean_cv_error <- mean(errors, na.rm = TRUE)
cat("RMSE cross-validation:", sqrt(mean_cv_error), "\n")
## RMSE cross-validation: 692.1672
model_no_random <- lm(sum_S2 ~ area * distance_ss_scaled + food + t_min_scaled + precip_scaled, 
                      data = locs_day)

errors_no_random <- numeric(length(folds))

for (i in seq_along(folds)) {
  train_data <- locs_day[-folds[[i]], ]
  test_data <- locs_day[folds[[i]], ]
  
  model <- lm(sum_S2 ~ area * distance_ss_scaled + food + t_min_scaled + precip_scaled, 
              data = train_data)
  
  predictions <- predict(model, newdata = test_data)
  
  errors_no_random[i] <- mean((predictions - test_data$sum_S2)^2, na.rm = TRUE)
}

mean_cv_error_no_random <- mean(errors_no_random, na.rm = TRUE)
cat("Mean RMSE without random effect:", sqrt(mean_cv_error_no_random), "\n")
## Mean RMSE without random effect: 692.2336

The linear mixed model indicates that capuchin group identity (random effect) accounts for some variation in daily travel distance, but the majority of the variance is explained by the fixed effects. The marginal R (0.147) suggests that environmental and spatial predictors explain about 15% of the variation, while the conditional R (0.149) shows that including the random effect adds little explanatory power. The RMSE values (692.17 vs.692.23) are nearly identical, reinforcing that group-level variation does not substantially improve predictive accuracy. However, significant fixed effectssuch as the interaction between study site and sleeping site distance, and greater travel distances in plantationshighlight the influence of habitat structure on capuchin movement patterns.

locs_day_pine <- locs_day %>% filter(area == 'Plantations')

dano <- read_csv ('files/dano_nuevo_area.csv')

dano <- dano %>% 
  separate(mes, 
           into = c("mes", "day"), 
           sep = "-") 
dano <- dano %>% 
  rename(year= day)

dano <- dano  %>%
  mutate(year = paste0("20", year))

dano$grupo <- factor(dano$grupo, 
                     levels = c('Grupo 1', 'Grupo 2', 'Grupo 3', 'Grupo 4'), 
                     labels = c('Columba', 'Pandemia', 'Triangulo', 'Gualicho'))

monthly_dano <- dano %>%
  group_by(grupo, mes, year) %>%
  summarise(media_dano = mean(m2, na.rm = TRUE)) 

monthly_dano$year <- as.integer(monthly_dano$year)

  rename(month = mes)

locs_day_pine$year <- as.integer(locs_day_pine$year)

  left_join(monthly_dano, by = c("grupo" = "grupo", "month" = "month", "year" = "year"))
